Ajay Banga is expected to bring transformative leadership to the World Bank as its President, focusing on core development goals and global challenges like climate change. The author, who has worked closely with Ajay since being elected Vice President, highlights their collaborative efforts in creating a new model of public-private partnership to address migration issues in Northern Central America. This partnership has already garnered over $4.2 billion in commitments from nearly 50 businesses and organizations, providing opportunities and hope for people in the region. The author praises Ajay's insight, energy, and persistence in promoting economic development and addressing the root causes of migration.